{% comment %}
Meal Plan — left or right half of a 1Lx1R mashup. Narrow and tall, so we stack
the next four days as compact rows.

Not using .item's .meta/.index for the weekday: the framework hard-codes
--item-meta-width to 10px (sized for a single-digit rank number), so any
multi-letter text put there overflows its box and overlaps .content
regardless of font-size. A .label--outline chip has no such fixed width, so
"Ons"/"Tors" sit cleanly on the same line as the meal text instead.

The chip needs an explicit min-width too — Swedish weekday abbreviations
aren't all the same length ("Fre" vs "Tors"), so without one each row's chip
renders at its own natural width and the meal text after it starts at a
different x per row. Fixing the width keeps every row's text flush.

Three levels need the framework's .stretch utility (flex: 1 1 0%; align-self:
stretch; min-width: 0), not just two:
  .item > .content        — .item only has this one flex child now that
                             .meta is gone, and .content has no flex-grow by
                             default, so without .stretch it's sized to its
                             own content instead of filling the row.
  .content > .flex (row)  — .item .content sets align-items:flex-start,
                             which shrink-wraps ITS children instead of
                             stretching them, so the label+title row also
                             needs .stretch to actually fill .content's now-
                             correct width.
  .flex > .title           — only once the row above has a real width does
                             flex-grow on the title mean anything; it's what
                             claims the space left over after the fixed-width
                             chip.
Skip any one of the three and the chain breaks the same way: TRMNL's own
data-clamp script measures whatever width the title ends up with, and on an
under-constrained chain that width is arbitrary — which is why a plain
"Lasagne" clamped down to "L…" while a much longer meal list on another row
rendered nearly in full.
{% endcomment %}
<div class="layout">
  <div class="grid grid--cols-1 gap--xsmall">
    {% for day in days limit:4 %}
      <div class="item">
        <div class="content stretch">
          <div class="flex flex--center-y gap--small stretch">
            <span class="label label--large label--outline" style="display: inline-block; min-width: 3.2em; text-align: center;">{{ day.dayName }}</span>
            <span class="title title--large stretch" data-clamp="1">
              {% if day.meals.size > 0 %}{{ day.meals | join: ", " }}{% else %}Inga måltider planerade{% endif %}
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="title_bar">
  <span class="title">Matsedel</span>
</div>
